HEADWORD: Primate
<hw>Pri"mate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>primat</ets>, F. <ets>primat</ets>, L. <ets>primas</ets>,
<ets>-atis</ets> one of the first, chief, fr. <ets>primus</ets> the
first. See <er>Prime</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
chief ecclesiastic in a national church; one who presides over other
bishops in a province; an archbishop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the Primates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Primates</ent>⟦br⟧
